The wheels seem to be working against one another. Has something changed? I heard that REV changed the libraries? Is this true? How do we work through this?

Do the wheels align, but spin in opposite directions?

If so, this is a common issue with having the wheel off by 180 degrees when using the calibration tool. One side of the calibration tool has a little circular cutout - make sure to orient the wheel such that the spur gear goes on this side.

Do the wheels not align?

Remember that you need to click “persist parameters” after you do the zero offset.

Hope this helps!
